node.text:
Sheep tribute: Ben Jackson a sheep farmer stuck in lockdown in New South Wales, was unable to attend his aunt Deb’s funeral… so he decided to honor her memory by creating a heart made from sheep that could be seen from heaven. He did so by strategically feeding but he laughs and says he had a couple of failed attempts and that one of the tries it looked like a sh*t emoji, and while he says Deb has a sense of humor… He wasn’t going to stop until she had the heart. 📹 #guyrajack via @michellemonaghan #somewhereiwouldliketolive
.
.
